Mrs Elspeth McGillicuddy has finshed her Christmas shopping shopping and is on her way to visit her old friend Jane Marple for Christmas. Her train passes another train running parallel and in the same direction as her train. Then, she sees a man with his back to her strangling a woman. She reports it to a sceptical ticket collectors and police who passes the report for investigation. When arriving at Miss Marple's cottage, she tells her the events and her fear that nothing will be done. Miss Marple believes her story, knowing her friend to be trustworthy in description. With no report of a body found in the next day's news, Miss Marple sets out to determine where the body is. With a good map and several rides on the trains Miss Marple, with the help of Lucy Eyelesbarrow, a young professional cook and housekeeper, target Rutherford Hall as the place to find the body.
